				<li id="16662691" class="cmnt-root" data="6" data-d="1651359175000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578765/Black-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">30 Apr 2022 18:52</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16662691" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">From personal experience with the incantation;<br/><br/>PVE: Great for bosses. Will apply a 20% reduction to the bosses max health allowing you to drop a boss 20% in your first hit. The draining effect from hitting the incantation is nice but for the FP cost is not worth in my opinion as I would rather use blackflame fireball for its HP drain effect at a much more efficient FP cost. I use this as a way to quickly remove 20% of a bosses health and then continue the fight as normal.<br/><br/>PVP: Pretty poor. It has a long wind-up which is really obvious making the actual projectile pretty easy to dodge. The damage for the wind-up is not particularly impressive either. Fortunately it does have the benefit of having high hyper armour meaning its really hard to break you out the spell. If you are invading it might be useful if it hits someone as a surprise but in a duel you will find very few opportunities to actually hit someone with the projectile. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16662691" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="butto