				<li id="16622303" class="cmnt-root" data="11" data-d="1650020927000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578765/Black-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">15 Apr 2022 07:08</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16622303" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">So fun fact. Based on the data shown, the 10% max health debuff does stack! But Few rules apply.<br/><br/>1, You can only stack Black Blade incantation&apos;s 10% max health debuff with either Maliketh&apos;s Black Blade or Black Knife&apos;s 10% max health debuff<br/>2, You cannot stack Maliketh&apos;s Black Blade&apos;s 10% max health debuff with Black Knife&apos;s.<br/>3, Under any circumstance the buff will not stack with itself, must be Black Blade incantation and one of your choices from above mentioned.<br/>4, Boss which is already under 80% health, the debuff stacking will do pretty much nothing.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16622303" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16622303" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">7</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>11</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1