				<li id="16569542" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1648197285000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578765/Black-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">25 Mar 2022 04:34</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16569542" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I dig further into how the 10% max health is being reduce and notice a &quot;bug&quot; or &quot;problem&quot; with any kind of temporary max health reduction form black blade, black knife or Maliketh&apos;s Black Blade. The thing is due to the way FromSoftware implemented it, the 10% max health reduction only kick in after your black blade or black knife&apos;s projectile due it own damage. <br/><br/>What dose that mean? If enemy has 100/100 health. Your projectile deal 20 damage and now enemy has 80/100 health, then their max health get reduced by 10% so enemy now has 80/90 health.<br/><br/>So basically not only the enemy never get that instant full 10% health reduction, but also the max health ticks is essentially lowered because now only 2% of 90 health. Some might think it is just temporary anyway what is the big deal? The thing is after the 10% health buff expired, enemy will not regain that health. It is similar to what happen if you put on the Primal Glint blade Talisman and put is off, Your reduced 50% health will not regain.<br/><br/>An ideal implementation or &quot;bug fix&quot; will be first applied the 10% max health reduction, so same example 90/90 health and then deal the damage. So player can at least  get a free small bleed on enemy. Also the 10% max health reduction will do nothing if target current health already below that point. But the sap is still pretty good.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16569542" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16569542" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>5</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16569542"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16569542" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16569542"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
