				<li id="16520026" class="cmnt-root" data="29" data-d="1647426158000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578765/Black-Blade" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">16 Mar 2022 06:22</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16520026" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">So, I tested this spell a fair bit on the two gargoyles at the &apos;Across the Roots&apos; grace.<br/>Using a Clawmark Seal+25, 46 Faith and 60 Strength<br/>Apparently the lower one on the roots takes a tock of about 411 damage and then another one while the flames tick up for just above 100 damage, this can result in killing it in one hit rather consistently.<br/>The one at the top though is a different issue entirely, as it seems to not get that second tick, no matter if the spell is charged or not. This hints at the earlier mentioned sweet spot range for the spell being just under the effective range of Giantsflame. Counterintuitively, the blade whirl part of the spell does no damage by itself.<br/>Additionally I am sure this doesn&apos;t profit from the Godfrey Icon (indeed, charging seems to not increase the damage at all, but might increase the sweet spot interval), the Radagon Icon, the Old Lord&apos;s Talisman in any meaningful way, but the Sacred Scorpion Talisman seems to add damage as expected by this being holy damage.<br/>Raising the Incant scaling from 288 by 6 via the Starscourge and Two Fingers Heirloom increases the damage of the initial hit from 411 to 420 giving us a 1.5 base for the initial hit and the total burn damage from 595 to 607, meaning the burn itself scales with 0.5.<br/><br/>I find myself a bit baffled as to where to place this spell to be honest. For such a late spell the scaling is merely okay, and easily outdone by Giantsflame. The saving grace of this one would be the maximum health reduction, but I do not think it stacks or lasts infinitely, as this spell clearly leaves the red &apos;downwards&apos; aura on enemies it hit. The research into this is more than a bit tricky, as I would need a spell that deals very quick ticks of damage to get an accurate measure of the health of a target to compare it with and without the effect.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16520026" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16520026" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>31</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16520026"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16520026" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16520026"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
